10/08/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- A total of 40 people, including 18 police officers, were arrested on Monday (August 9th) for corruption. The arrests were part of an investigation into fraud allegations involving transportation tenders at the Istanbul Police Department. This is the second wave of arrests in the anti-corruption sweep. The first, on July 30th, led to 69 arrests, including 15 police officers. (Vatan - 10/08/10; Sabah - 09/08/10)
